        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "ASTM F1717 single loading condition (static compression-bending at 10° offset). Only one test condition evaluated; multi-condition or fatigue testing not included in this COU."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under the single standardized ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition. The standard does not mandate multiple loading angles or rates for this device class. While Gradation 2 would require at least two distinct test conditions to bracket the operating envelope, the regulatory submission strategy accepts the single-condition limitation given that ASTM F1717 is the FDA-recognized consensus standard for pedicle screw constructs. This shortfall is addressed by the offset rationale in the decision record."
